# Get Started

## Setup Python Environment

Python 3.7.0 (I doubt it works on any Python 2.x)

Dependent Modules:
	- flask
	- urllib
	- bs4 (beautiful soup)
	- sqlite3
	- matplotlib

How I installed Modules:

```
pip3 install <module name>
```

## Run setup.py

> This script creates database, creates table, scrapes data, inserts to table and generate the image.

Go to the base folder. You should see "app.py". Simply run:

```
python setup.py
```

or 

```
python3 setup.py
```

Expected output:

```
Create database done!
Web scraping done!
Insert data done!
Image generation done!
```

## Run app.py

> This scrips starts the web server

Go to the base folder. You should see "app.py". Simply run:

```
python app.py
```

or 

```
python3 app.py
```

Expected output: 
```
Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000/ (Press CTRL+C to quit)
```

# References

## Technology stack

1. Flask: python web application framework
- http://flask.pocoo.org/
- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WfpFUmV1d0w

2. Beautiful Soup: python library to parse html
- https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/bs4/doc/

3. SQLlite: simple SQL database engine
- https://www.sqlite.org/index.html
